column1: 1/ World Bank country code for Democratic Republic of Congo is ZAR.
2/ Kosovo does not have a country code assigned by ISO and is not included in the UN M49 country list. The ODW code KSV is adopted from the World Bank.
3/ World Bank country code for Romania is ROM.
4/ Sark (UN country code 680) does not have a unique ISO code. It is included in ISO code GGY (Guernsey). The ODW code GGS is assigned to Sark to maintain alignment with the UN system
5/ Country name of Swaziland changed to Eswatini.
